    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Sarang Joshi's Website","author":"Sarang Joshi"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"13f67235-b8d9-545d-9684-3ccede6d0c51","excerpt":"So I recently built a PC, and had to get my full development environment set up again. It was quite a hassle, primarily because I hadn’t properly written down…","html":"<p>So I recently built a PC, and had to get my full development environment set up again. It was quite a hassle, primarily because I hadn’t properly written down what I had done to set it up on my laptop for all these years. This document should ensure that that doesn’t happen again.</p>\n<h1 id=\"windows-installation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#windows-installation\" aria-label=\"windows installation permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Windows Installation</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-win10\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">WSL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/ubuntu-1804-lts/9n9tngvndl3q\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Ubuntu 18.04</a> (the latest Ubuntu distro at the time of writing)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mintty/wsltty\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">wsltty</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://atom.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Atom</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/cascadia-code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Cascadia Code</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://git-scm.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Git for Windows</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"atom\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#atom\" aria-label=\"atom permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Atom</h1>\n<p>Restore backup for Atom with <code class=\"language-text\">sync-settings</code>, with a new <code class=\"language-text\">Personal Access Token</code> with <code class=\"language-text\">gist</code> access: <a href=\"https://github.com/settings/tokens/new\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/settings/tokens/new</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"ps-why-atom-why-not-the-shinier-vs-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ps-why-atom-why-not-the-shinier-vs-code\" aria-label=\"ps why atom why not the shinier vs code permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>P.S.: Why Atom? Why not the shinier VS Code?</h2>\n<p>I use vim mode in Atom. VS Code has (had?) an issue where scrolling past a closed (folded) code block would cause it to open. So I got used to Atom. I believe it’s been fixed, so at some point I need to give VS Code a serious try.</p>\n<h1 id=\"vs-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#vs-code\" aria-label=\"vs code permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>VS Code</h1>\n<p>Giving it a try now! Let’s see how this goes.</p>\n<h2 id=\"issues\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#issues\" aria-label=\"issues permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Issues</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Settings sync doesn’t sync WSL settings very cleanly. Current extensions:</li>\n</ul>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Name</th>\n<th>Package name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Atom Keymap</td>\n<td>ms-vscode.atom-keybindings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>GitLens</td>\n<td>eamodio.gitlens</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Markdown All in One</td>\n<td>yzhang.markdown-all-in-one</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Prettier</td>\n<td>esbenp.prettier-vscode</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Python</td>\n<td>ms-python.python</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>TSLint</td>\n<td>ms-vscode.vscode-typescript-tslint-plugin</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h1 id=\"wsltty\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#wsltty\" aria-label=\"wsltty permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>WSLtty</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Set <code class=\"language-text\">wsltty</code> settings\n<ul>\n<li>Text\n<ul>\n<li>Font: <code class=\"language-text\">Cascadia Code</code></li>\n<li>Size: <code class=\"language-text\">14pt</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Looks\n<ul>\n<li>Cursor: <code class=\"language-text\">Block</code>, not blinking</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Terminal\n<ul>\n<li>Bell: <code class=\"language-text\">no beep</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"wsl\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#wsl\" aria-label=\"wsl permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>WSL</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Turn off password for <code class=\"language-text\">sudo</code> access:\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">$ sudo visudo</code></li>\n<li>Add line at the bottom: <code class=\"language-text\">sarang ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL</code> (beware the fearful editor, Nano!)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Move home directory:\n<ul>\n<li>Edit <code class=\"language-text\">/etc/passwd</code> and change <code class=\"language-text\">/home/sarang</code> in the current user’s line (most likely at the bottom) to <code class=\"language-text\">/mnt/c/Users/&lt;WINDOWS USERNAME></code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Turn off <code class=\"language-text\">command-not-found</code>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">$ sudo apt remove command-not-found command-not-found-data</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Set up <code class=\"language-text\">/etc/wsl.conf</code> file:\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">[automount]\noptions = \"metadata,umask=0033\"</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>Clone and install dotfiles:\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ mkdir -p ~/git &amp;&amp; cd ~/git\n$ git clone git@github.com:sarangjo/dotfiles.git\n$ cd ~/git/dotfiles\n$ ./install.sh</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"vim\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#vim\" aria-label=\"vim permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Vim</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Install <a href=\"https://www.vim.org/download.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GVim for Windows</a></li>\n<li>Install Vundle and <code class=\"language-text\">vim</code> packages\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ git clone https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim\n$ vim\n:VundleInstall</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"nodejs-and-yarn\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nodejs-and-yarn\" aria-label=\"nodejs and yarn permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NodeJS and Yarn</h1>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://nodejs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">NodeJS</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Do the WSL installation first, so that <code class=\"language-text\">n</code> doesn’t get confused by node in PATH.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Windows: <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://nodejs.org/en/</a></li>\n<li>WSL (using <a href=\"https://github.com/tj/n\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">n</a>)\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ sudo apt install -y make\n$ curl -L https://git.io/n-install | bash</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><a href=\"https://yarnpkg.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Yarn</a></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Windows: <a href=\"https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install#windows-stable\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install#windows-stable</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>WSL:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ curl -sS https://dl.yarnpkg.com/debian/pubkey.gpg | sudo apt-key add -\n$ echo \"deb https://dl.yarnpkg.com/debian/ stable main\" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/yarn.list\n$ # exclude the nodejs install\n$ sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install -y --no-install-recommends yarn</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"python-27-and-37\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#python-27-and-37\" aria-label=\"python 27 and 37 permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Python 2.7 and 3.7</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ sudo apt install -y python2.7 python3.7 python3.7-venv</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"mongodb\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mongodb\" aria-label=\"mongodb permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>MongoDB</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>WSL installation: <a href=\"https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"misc\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#misc\" aria-label=\"misc permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Misc</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ sudo apt install -y exuberant-ctags</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"wip\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#wip\" aria-label=\"wip permalink\" class=\"visible-autolink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>WIP</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>MSYS2\n<ul>\n<li>Modify the Mingw x64 start menu shortcut to have <code class=\"language-text\">-full-path</code></li>\n<li>Set <code class=\"language-text\">%HOME%</code> to home directory</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>PHP</li>\n<li>ConEmu/Cmder?</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"3 min read"}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Development Environment Setup","date":"November 04, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/tech/dev-env-setup/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/tech/windows/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Developing Software on Windows"}}}},
